  <section id="quando" class="seasonSection">
    <h2>When they can be captured</h2>
    <div class="seasonPanel">
      <ul class="seasonChecklist">
        <li>Altar conquest starts in week 3 of Season 6.</li>
        <li>Altars unlock progressively week by week.</li>
        <li>Availability follows this schedule:</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="tableWrap seasonTableWrap">
      <table class="table seasonTable">
        <thead><tr><th>Week</th><th>Available Altars</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Week 3</td><td>Level 1 Altar + Level 2 Altar</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Week 4</td><td>Level 3 Altar is added</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Week 5</td><td>Level 4 Altar is added</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Week 6</td><td>Level 5 Altar is added</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="seasonPanel seasonCallout"><p><b>Note:</b> always verify the exact time in game, because it can depend on server time and active events.</p></div>
  </section>

  <section id="regole" class="seasonSection">
    <h2>Attack and conquest rules</h2>
    <div class="seasonGrid seasonGrid2">
      <div class="seasonPanel"><ul class="seasonChecklist"><li>Altars become attackable only during the event windows.</li><li>The alliance does not freely choose the time: it is normally set by the game/server.</li><li>The alliance decides which Altars to contest, who garrisons and who attacks.</li><li>If the Altar is neutral, the alliance that completes conquest according to event rules wins.</li></ul></div>
      <div class="seasonPanel"><ul class="seasonChecklist"><li>If the Altar is occupied, you must overcome/destroy the defense and complete conquest within the available window.</li><li>If no alliance completes conquest, the Altar may stay with the previous owner or follow the game progress rules.</li><li>Altars are strategic because they provide special alliance abilities.</li><li>Coordinate before the window opens: choose target, rallies, defenders, reinforcements and R4/R5 roles.</li></ul></div>
    </div>
    <div class="seasonPanel seasonCallout"><h3>Operational tip</h3><p>Do not attack Altars randomly. Before the window, decide the priority Altar, who leads the attack, who defends and which players must keep troops ready.</p></div>
  </section>

  <section id="abilita" class="seasonSection">
    <h2>Abilities and benefits</h2>
    <div class="tableWrap seasonTableWrap altarAbilityTableWrap">
      <table class="table seasonTable altarAbilityTable">
        <thead><tr><th>Level</th><th>Altar</th><th>Ability</th><th>Benefit</th><th>Recommended use</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Level 1</td><td>Snake Altar</td><td>Snake Barrier / Fortify</td><td>Creates a defensive shield on one city of your faction.</td><td>Defend important cities before wars or PvP windows.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Level 2</td><td>Echo Altar</td><td>Night Army / Mummy Army</td><td>Summons an army that periodically attacks enemies in an area.</td><td>Offensive pressure against exposed bases or poorly defended enemy zones.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Level 3</td><td>Gust Altar</td><td>Serpent Breath / Warlord Missile</td><td>Launches an area attack against enemy bases and can create strong territorial pressure.</td><td>Coordinated offense against enemy base clusters or strategic zones.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Level 4</td><td>Feather Altar</td><td>Thunder Feathers / Tesla Coil</td><td>Periodically hits nearby enemy bases, causing durability damage.</td><td>Area control and defense of key cities or positions.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Level 5</td><td>Treehaven Altar</td><td>Tranquil Rewind / Refresh</td><td>Reduces or resets the cooldown of an alliance skill, allowing quick reuse.</td><td>Decisive battles, double use of important skills, strong strategic value.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="strategia" class="seasonSection">
    <h2>Recommended strategy</h2>
    <div class="seasonGrid seasonGrid2"><div class="seasonPanel"><ul class="seasonChecklist"><li>For defensive alliances: prioritize Snake + Feather + Treehaven.</li><li>For offensive and coordinated alliances: prioritize Gust + Echo + Treehaven.</li><li>For medium or weaker alliances: target defensive Altars useful for city protection first.</li><li>Treehaven is very strong because it lets you reuse important skills at decisive moments.</li><li>Altar choices must be made before the conquest window, not during it.</li></ul></div>
      <div class="tableWrap seasonTableWrap"><table class="table seasonTable"><thead><tr><th>Alliance situation</th><th>Recommended priority</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Defensive alliance</td><td>Snake + Feather + Treehaven</td></tr><tr><td>Offensive alliance</td><td>Gust + Echo + Treehaven</td></tr><tr><td>Medium/weak alliance</td><td>Snake first, then evaluate Feather or Treehaven</td></tr><tr><td>Very active R4/R5</td><td>Treehaven is very important to reuse decisive skills</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>
  </section>

  <section id="checklist" class="seasonSection"><h2>Checklist before the Altar window</h2><ul class="seasonChecklist seasonPillList"><li>Decidere l’Altar obiettivo.</li><li>Communicate time and target in alliance chat.</li><li>Prepare rallies and reinforcements.</li><li>Define who attacks and who defends.</li><li>Keep healing and speedups ready.</li><li>Avoid random uncoordinated attacks.</li><li>Monitor nearby enemy alliances.</li><li>Use skills only when they are truly needed.</li></ul></section>
</section>

